The ‘Bring Back Our Girls’ movement has marked the 2,000th day of the abduction of Chibok Schoolgirls. Taking to its Twitter handle @BBOG_Nigeria on Saturday, the organisers had tweeted: “Today we mark #2000Days since our #ChibokGirls have been held in continuous captivity. “112 #ChibokGirls have not enjoyed being free for 2,000 days. “Today and until they return, we demand #BringBackOurGirls.” See the photographs, courtesy, BBOG: 